  "market_context": "ES1! weekly chart showing price action that failed to displace below a prior swing low, setting up a retracement scenario where the analyst illustrates the cyclical movement between external range liquidity (swing high/low) and internal range liquidity (fair value gap).",
  "key_observation": "After failing to displace below an old swing low, price retraced into the fair value gap (internal liquidity), then reached up for an old high (external liquidity), demonstrating the external-to-internal-to-external delivery cycle on the weekly timeframe.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified that price failed to displace below an old swing low on the ES1! weekly chart, signalling a potential retracement higher.",
    "Anticipated price would reach for the fair value gap above as the next internal range liquidity target.",
    "Confirmed price reached into the fair value gap (internal liquidity).",
    "Noted that if the fair value gap was not respected, price would continue to reach for the old high (external liquidity), which it did.",
    "Observed that after taking the external high, a new fair value gap formed, providing fresh internal liquidity for the next cycle.",
    "Referenced the daily bias logic: since price failed to displace below the previous bar and closed back inside, the next candle should reach higher into the internal liquidity.",
    "Projected that if price continues respecting the internal FVG and moves lower, it would then reach for external liquidity (the swing low) to complete the cycle."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Price oscillates between external range liquidity (swing highs/lows) and internal range liquidity (fair value gaps). After taking one, anticipate the other as the next draw on liquidity — this cycle provides a framework for projecting weekly directional targets.",
